---
import BaseLayout from '@/layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About Us"
  description="Learn about our robotics club, our mission, and our team of student engineers."
>
  <div class="py-12 text-center">
    <div class="container mx-auto px-4 max-w-4xl">
      <!-- Header -->
      <header class="mb-12">
        <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">
          About Our Voorheesville Robotics Club
        </h1>
        <p class="text-xl text-gray-600">
          Inspiring the next generation of engineers and innovators
        </p>
      </header>

      <!-- Content -->
      <div class="prose prose-lg prose-gray max-w-none">
        <h2>Our Mission</h2>
        <p>
          We're a student-led middle/high school robotics club dedicated to learning through hands-on
          engineering challenges. Our mission is to inspire students to pursue careers in STEM
          fields by providing practical experience in robotics, programming, and teamwork.
        </p>

        <h2>What We Do</h2>
        <p>Throughout the year, our club members elect activities they would like to pursue. These could include:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Design and build robots for competitions like FIRST Robotics and VEX</li>
          <li>Learn programming languages including Python, C++, and Arduino</li>
          <li>Use CAD software to design mechanical components</li>
          <li>Work with electronics, sensors, and motor controllers</li>
          <li>Collaborate on team projects and share knowledge</li>
          <li>Participate in regional and national competitions</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Meeting Schedule</h2>
        <p>
          <strong>Regular Meetings:</strong> We meet every Monday (Grades 9-12), Wednesday (Grades 9-12) and Thursday (Grades 6-12) from 2:30-3:30 PM in Room 154<br>
          <strong>Build Sessions:</strong> None Scheduled <br>
          <strong>Competition Season:</strong> None Scheduled
        </p>

        <h2>Club History</h2>
        <p>
          Founded in September 2025, our club has fostered a learning enviorment to over 20 active participants.
          
        </p>

        <h2>Achievements</h2>
        

        <h2>Get Involved</h2>
        <p>
          Interested in joining? No experience necessary! We welcome students of all skill levels.
          Come to any Monday or Thursday meeting to learn more or <a href="/contact">contact us</a> for more information.
        </p>

        <p>
          <strong>Contact us:</strong> jwinter@voorheesville.org<br>
          <strong>Follow us:</strong> <a href="https://github.com">GitHub</a> |
          <a href="https://youtube.com">YouTube</a> |
          <a href="https://discord.com">Discord</a>
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
